Package: gscope
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Lightweight Linux scope isolation library
 gscope is a production-grade C library for creating isolated execution
 environments on Linux using namespaces, cgroups v2, OverlayFS, and
 seccomp-bpf.
 .
 Features:
  - Namespace isolation (PID, NET, MNT, UTS, IPC, USER)
  - Cgroup v2 resource limits (CPU, memory, PIDs, I/O)
  - OverlayFS + pivot_root
  - seccomp-bpf syscall filtering
  - Netlink networking (no subprocess)
  - Template executor for automated provisioning
  - gscopectl CLI tool
 .
 This package contains the shared library, CLI tool, and development headers.

Package: libgscope-dev
Architecture: linux-any
Section: libdevel
Depends: gscope (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Lightweight Linux scope isolation library - development files
 Development headers for libgscope.
 .
 This package contains the C headers needed to develop applications
 using the gscope library.
